The Lagos State Governor, Babajide Sanwo-Olu is currently in Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital. Sanwo-Olu was received by Governor Dapo Abiodun at the Presidential Lodge, Ibara Housing Estate, Abeokuta. The Lagos State governor arrived the Gateway State at noon for a meeting with Abiodun. The Senior Special Assistant to Gov Abiodun on New Media, Emmanuel Ojo, told DAILY POST correspondent that the meeting was “for the official launching of Lagos-Ogun Joint Development Commission.” DAILY POST reports that Ogun is the only state sharing boundaries with Lagos. Both Abiodun and Sanwo-Olu are members of the All Progressives Congress (APC). 